A: The issue is with this line:
names.add(dataSnapshot.getChildren().iterator().next().getValue(String.class));

You are getting the iterator of all children and then getting the first element of that iterator. This will always give you the first child's value.
Instead, you should use the iterator of the current loop iteration:
names.add(dataSnapshot1.getValue(String.class));

So your code should look like this:
for (DataSnapshot dataSnapshot1:dataSnapshot.getChildren()) {
    i = i + 1;
    names.add(dataSnapshot1.getValue(String.class));
}

This way, you are getting the value of the current child in each iteration of the loop.

